ce:section.ce:para:
To evaluate the efficacy of the artificial intelligence handheld sensor, standard recovery experiments were implemented to quantify Ni2+ and EDTA in various real samples. As demonstrated in Table 1
                        , the recoveries of Ni2+ in various water, spinach, and milk samples are measured to be 98.88 %–105.40 %, 99.78 %–106.30 %, and 99.04 %–100.58 %, respectively. The recoveries of EDTA in various water, shampoo and bread samples are determined as 98.47 %–100.49 %, 100.98 %–102.13 %, and 99.40 %–100.73 %, respectively (Table 2
                        ). Such an outcome corroborates the feasibility of proposed method that could be devoted for user-friendly in-field quantification of Ni2+ and EDTA in real samples.
